<L><NOTE N="&ast;" PLACE="foot">All along this coa&s;t, the ancient <HI>Romans</HI> had their winter re|treats; and &s;everal populous cities &s;tood.</NOTE> Where, when &s;oft &s;uns and tepid winters ro&s;e,</L>
<L>Rejoicing crouds inhal'd the balm of peace;</L>
<L>Where city'd hill to hill reflected blaze;<MILESTONE N="305"></L>
<L>And where, with <HI>Ceres, Bacchus</HI> wont to hold</L>
<L>A genial &s;trife. Her youthful form, robu&s;t,</L>
