<L>Of GREECE I vary'd; who&s;e unmixing &s;tates,</L>
<L>By the keen &s;oul of emulation pierc'd,<MILESTONE N="80"></L>
<L>Long wag'd alone the bloodle&s;s war of arts,</L>
<L>And their <HI>be&s;t</HI> empire gain'd. But to diffu&s;e</L>
<L>O'er <HI>Men</HI> an empire was my purpo&s;e now:</L>
<L>To let my martial maje&s;ty abroad;</L>
<L><PB N="284" REF="55">
Into the vortex of one State to draw<MILESTONE N="85"></L>
<L>The whole mix'd Force, and Liberty, on earth;</L>
<L>To conquer Tyrants, and &s;et Nations free.</L>
<L>Already have I given, with flying touch,</L>
<L>A broken view of this my ample&s;t reign.</L>
<L>Now, while its fir&s;t, la&s;t, periods you &s;urvey,<MILESTONE N="90"></L>
<L>Mark how it lab'ring ro&s;e, and rapid fell.</L>
<L>When ROME in noon tide empire gra&s;p'd the world,</L>
<L>And, &s;oon as her re&s;i&s;tle&s;s legions &s;hone,</L>
<L>The nations &s;toop'd around; tho' then appear'd</L>
<L>Her grandeur mo&s;t, yet in her dawn of power,<MILESTONE N="95"></L>
<L>By many a jealous equal people pre&s;s'd,</L>
<L>Then was the toil, the mighty &s;truggle then;</L>
