<L>What e'er high fancy, &s;ound judicious thought,</L>
<L>An ample generous heart, undrooping &s;oul,</L>
<L>And firm tenacious valour can be&s;tow.<MILESTONE N="80"></L>
<L>Great nur&s;e of fruits, of flocks, of commerce, SHE!</L>
<L>Great nur&s;e of men! By THEE, O GODDESS, taught,</L>
<L>Her old renown I trace, di&s;clo&s;e her &s;ource</L>
<L>Of wealth, of grandeur; and to BRITONS &s;ing</L>
<L>A &s;train the Mu&s;es never touch'd before.<MILESTONE N="85"></L>
