<L>Thus nations &s;ink, &s;ociety di&s;&s;olves;<MILESTONE N="115"></L>
<L>Rapine and guile and violence break loo&s;e,</L>
<L>Everting li&s;e, and turning love to gall;</L>
<L>Man hates the face of man, and <HI>Indian</HI> woods</L>
<L>And <HI>Lybia's</HI> hi&s;&s;ing &s;ands to him are tame.</L>
<L>By tho&s;e THREE VIRTUES be the frame &s;u&s;tain'd</L>
<L>Of BRITISH FREIDOM: INDEPENDENT LIFE;<MILESTONE N="121"></L>
<L>INTEGRITY IN OFFICE; and o'er all</L>
